@@.mc-thoughts; The key warms in your palm. You have just enough time to think //wards// before the room agrees with you.@@<br>
@@.mc-thoughts; Something cool and wet finds your wrist. Then your other wrist. Then somewhere your wrists aren't. The chair holds you to itself. Khadija's house, it turns out, keeps its own counsel about thieves -- one length tight enough at your throat to make the breath count, another working low and patient, getting acquainted before it@@
<<linkappend "@@.usebtn; gets to work.@@">>
